                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d275">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/6081: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">Then in France, to the <gloss type="to"
                            >Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">St. Jean de Luz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-27T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 27, 1937—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 27—9:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>314. David Darrah, <hi rend="italic">Chicago Tribune</hi>, informed me this
                    morning that he saw General Teruzzi, head of Mussolini’s Fascist militia in
                    Spanish uniform in San Sebastian yesterday, and that colleagues have told him
                    General Badoglio has arrived also in Spain and also wears such uniform.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
